<TITLE> Education ministry, Microsoft sign deal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 25 (bdnews24.com)The education ministry on Tuesday signed an agreement with software giant Microsoft to train the secondary school teachers on basic computing. Acting education secretary Ujjal Bikash Dutt and country manager for Microsoft Bangladesh Firoz Mahmud signed the agreement at a ceremony at the Secretariat. Education minister Nurul Islam Nahid and additional secretary Razia Begum were present at the ceremony. The minister thanked Microsoft for their assistance and said, "Initiatives from the local and foreign private organisations would help to build an IT-based education system." The agreement, effective from July, will run through to June 28, 2013. Microsoft Bangladesh initiated training for more than 8,000 teachers on basic computing after an agreement struck on Dec 5, 2005 in presence of Microsoft chairman Bill Gates. bd
